Direct Known Subclasses:
Dijkstra, DijkstraNative
 class DijkstraBase
extends java.lang.Object

Diskstra's single source shortest path algorithm. Dijkstra's algorithm is a single source shortest path algorithm working on directed graphs with non-negative edge weights. If the graph is acyclic, AcyclicSP supplies a faster algorithm.

Method Detail

setPQueue

public void setPQueue(PQueue<Node> pq)
Allow setting the priority queue for this dijkstra instance.

Note:

The priority queue not only defines the data structure in which node distances are managed, but also defines the comparator for a node. Hence, one can use this method to define a priority queue which implements A* search with a heuristic function h. The queue should order the priorities by the sum of the distance map and the heuristic for each node.

Parameters:
pq - a priority queue.
